Reasoning: The paper deals with the evaluation of Near-infrared imaging in semantic scene segmentation using deep learning. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning models for semantic segmentation makes it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the use of NIR imaging for outdoor scenes makes it relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
